Foot & mouth disease - Brazil 20000825.1422
Foot & mouth disease - Brazil: OIE report 20000824.1408
Date: 26 Aug 2000
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: OIE

[Below is the text of an OIE report - Mod.PC
Emergency report
Translation of an e-mail received on 24 Aug 2000 from Dr Hamilton Ricardo
Farias, Director, Department of Animal Welfare, Ministry of Agriculture and
Supply, Brasilia:
Report date: 23 Aug 2000.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: 23 Aug 2000.
Estimated date of first infection: 10 Aug 2000.
Outbreaks:
Joia municipality, State of Rio Grande do Sul (28ยบ 39' S - 54ยบ 07' W)

Description of affected population: traditional dairy herd producing milk
for local consumption.
Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
species susceptible cases deaths destroyed slaughtered
bov (1) 216 28 0 ... ...
sui (2) 6 0 0 ... ...
(1) 31 <4 months, 55 between 4 and 12 months, 38 between 12 and 24 months,
23 between 24 and 36 months, 69 >36 months
(2) 6 young animals
Diagnosis:
A. Laboratory where diagnosis was made: Laboratory of Animal Welfare,
Ministry of Agriculture and Supply, Recife, Pernambuco.
B. Causal agent: FMD virus type O.
Epidemiology:
A. Source of agent / origin of infection: investigations under way.
B. Mode of spread: investigations under way.

Translation of an extract from a communication sent to the Pan American
Foot-and-Mouth Disease Center on 23 Aug 2000 by Dr Hamilton Ricardo Farias:
Control measures to be implemented:
a) declaration of an animal health state of emergency in the Municipality
of Joia. The entire territory of this municipality is considered as a
surveillance zone. Ban on moving animals susceptible to foot and mouth
disease (FMD) and potentially contaminated products. Out of this zone, the
area of which could be extended, depending on the results of the
epidemiological investigations;
b) slaughter and destruction of all animals susceptible to FMD present in
the outbreaks. Restocking, authorized only after cleaning and disinfection
has been completed and a suitable period of time has elapsed;
Restocking with sentinel animals placed under official surveillance;
c) epidemiological investigation to determine the origin of the outbreaks
and to look for any evidence of spread;
d) examination of the surveillance activities implemented in the State of
Rio Grande do Sul.
--
